                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The General Assembly, at its Fourth Session, dealt with (1) the question of a
                    permanent international regime for the Jerusalem area and the protection of the
                    Holy Places and (2) the question of assistance to Palestinian refugees.</p>
                <p>The <hi rend="italic">Ad Hoc</hi> Political Committee of the Assembly devoted 13
                    meetings to the first of these matters, from November 24 to 29 and from December
                    5 to 7. The Committee’s proceedings during the earlier of these periods are
                    printed in United Nations, <hi rend="italic">Official Records of the Fourth
                        Session of the General Assembly, Ad Hoc Political Committee, Summary Records
                        of Meetings, 27 September–7 December 1949</hi> (hereinafter identified as
                        <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>
                    <hi rend="italic">4th sess., Ad Hoc Political Committee</hi>), pages
                    246–306.</p>
                <p>Several proposals were offered to the Committee and on November 29, general
                    debate concluded, whereupon Subcommittee 1 was appointed to examine the
                    proposals (<hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>., page 305).</p>
            </div>
